  "body": "\r\n#### System information\r\n**Geth version:** \r\nVersion: 1.8.12-unstable\r\nGit Commit: 78e03595aff47b5c608896b3d07dca84ec3b6638\r\nArchitecture: amd64\r\nProtocol Versions: [63 62]\r\nNetwork Id: 1\r\nGo Version: go1.9.2\r\nOperating System: linux\r\n\r\n**OS & Version:**\r\nUbuntu 16.04.3 LTS (GNU/Linux 4.4.0-1047-aws x86_64)\r\n\r\n#### Expected behaviour\r\nshh_subscribe handles partial topics correclty\r\n\r\n#### Actual behaviour\r\nshh_subscribe returns error on receiving partial topic\r\n\r\n```\r\n{\"jsonrpc\":\"2.0\",\"id\":2,\"method\":\"shh_subscribe\",\"params\":[\"messages\",{\"topics\":[\"0x332211\"],\"symKeyID\":\"65f17a19d311f19d8ae860a76387426f12e82e7ef52879e43312a46ddd3d6f52\"}]}\r\n{\"jsonrpc\":\"2.0\",\"id\":2,\"error\":{\"code\":-32602,\"message\":\"invalid argument 1: hex string has length 6, want 8 for Topic\"}}\r\n\r\n```\r\n#### Steps to reproduce the behaviour\r\n1. Create a symmetric key\r\n2. Try to call a method shh_subscribe with a topic less than a 4 bytes in length\r\n\r\n",
